            "last_activity_date": 1376377543,
            "creation_date": 1376377021,
            "body": "<ul>\n<li>remove <code>IF EXISTS<\/code><\/li>\n<li>use <code>user_name='example'<\/code> (with quotes) or even better <code>user_name=?<\/code> with PreparedStatement<\/li>\n<li>use <code>preparedStatement.executeUpdate()<\/code><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p><strong>it shouldnt throw any error even if no result<\/strong><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 18202556,
            "question_id": 18202377,
            "last_edit_date": 1376377543
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9c7d0acde3db4a3a725ee6d537eebf83?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1479453,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1389153,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1389153/christopher-stock",
                "reputation": 1445,
                "display_name": "Christopher Stock"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1376376847,
            "creation_date": 1376376847,
            "body": "<p>I think you just forgot the apostrophs that span the String literal 'example':<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>DELETE FROM users WHERE user_name='example'.\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The 'WHERE EXISTS' is unnecessary here!<\/p>\n\n<p>Greetings<\/p>\n\n<p>Christopher<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 18202513,
            "question_id": 18202377
        },
        {
